China Monetary Tightening to Persist Next Few Years, CLSA Says

-- B y   D a r r e n   B o e y
-- 
2011-09-19T07:53:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/china-monetary-tightening-to-persist-next-few-years-clsa-says.html
  China ’s tight monetary policies
will persist “in the next few years” with “periodic
relaxation” including in 2012 to sustain economic growth,
according to Manop Sangiambut, CLSA Asia-Pacific Markets’ head
of China A-share research.  CLSA is “underweight” property developers amid the
possibility of slowing sales, Sangiambut told reporters in  Hong
Kong  today. The government will be careful in lifting property
curbs on concern prices will “skyrocket,” he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
